{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegality over the last century has halted research on the many new psychoactive substances that have been discovered in that time \\(as well as traditional ones\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Citizens would not have to worry about potentially losing their career over using a substance for a medical condition. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The criminalization of drug use is the major agitator of the economic rifts caused by drug use: illegal drug use leads to arrests which lead to arrest records and the socially imposed inability to self-produce wealth.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has released inaccurate or untruthful information about drugs in an attempt to stop the public from using them. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legal sellers will be highly scrutinized and won't want to risk losing their license. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The evidence suggests that criminalisation does not significantly decrease drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load offâ€¦ So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The law regulation of the drug's market will standardize the quality of the products, and their safety, creating incentives for the consumers to prefer to deal in the legal market. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}
